# Build context exclusion list. Anything not listed here is uploaded to the
# Docker daemon on every build — keep this aggressive.
#
# The COPY directives in Dockerfile.bot / Dockerfile.web are the source of
# truth for what ends up in images; entries here only affect what's *available*
# to those COPYs.

# --- VCS ---------------------------------------------------------------------
.git/
.github/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- Python ------------------------------------------------------------------
.venv/
.venv-easyocr-bench/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.cache/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ty-cache/
.ty-baseline.json
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/

# --- Node / Next.js ----------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
web/node_modules/
web/.next/
web/out/
web/.turbo/
web/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo

# --- Editor / IDE / agent state ---------------------------------------------
.idea/
.vscode/
.claude/
.cursor/
*.swp
*~

# --- OS junk -----------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Secrets / per-host data -------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
.env.local
.env.*.local
!.env.example
.npmrc
npmrc
pip.conf
auth.json
.secrets/
src/config/_telemetry_secrets.py
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
# Durable runtime state: configured devices, accounts, player ids, queues,
# screenshots metadata, and SQLCipher sidecars. Never upload it to the Docker
# daemon or bake it into images; prod compose mounts a fresh named volume here.
db/state/
src/modules/notify/data/
# Per-host license file lives in the bind-mounted ``license-data`` dir at
# runtime; never bake one into the image.
license-data/*.json
license-data/*.jwt
license-data/*.bak
license-data/host-id
# Trial / personal license JWTs sometimes dropped at repo root for local
# testing — never leak these into the build context.
*.licence.jwt
*.license.jwt

# --- Docker / CI artifacts (image doesn't need its own build inputs) --------
Dockerfile*
docker-compose*.yml
.dockerignore

# --- Logs / scratch ----------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
coverage/
htmlcov/
runs/
captures/
.tmp_ocr/
temporal/

# --- Test code (not needed at runtime) ---------------------------------------
**/tests/
**/test_*.py
**/conftest.py
!src/config/test_module.py
# Runtime references stay in the image, but pending Labeling captures and
# pytest rehearsal frames do not. They are recreated locally as needed and can
# otherwise add tens of megabytes to every bot build context.
**/references/temporal/
**/references/rehearsal/fixtures/

# --- Local-only / unused-at-runtime directories ------------------------------
# Not COPY'd by Dockerfile.bot / Dockerfile.web — keeping them out of the
# build context shaves seconds off ``docker build`` and keeps the daemon's
# tar upload small.
stubs/
data/                  # kNN training images (training pipeline only)
temporal/              # runtime scratch — regenerated per tick
docs/                  # docs site sources
grafana/               # local Grafana provisioning
modules/               # pre-Phase-3 module tree (replaced by games/)
draft/                 # WIP / scratch
page/                  # standalone submodule (not consumed by bot image)
cmd/                   # standalone helper scripts
.streamlit/            # legacy Streamlit config
